title: For Sale/Trade:  Nazi mauser k98
postcontent: Here we have a very interesting 1944 Nazi Mauser K98 made by BNZ Steyr-Daimler-puch. 8mm mauser, 23.62" barrel. The gun has a single Rune mark on the receiver, which means it was made for the Nazi SS. The gun also has late war re-work/numbered componets, as well as the "x" indicating Russian capture. I'm not sure if the Germans mixed parts or the Russians, but the gun is not matching serial numbers. That adds a pretty neat component to this gun becasue at some point in the war it was taken from a Nazi solder either dead or alive and repurposed for the Russian war effort. My guess is if a Russian was taking your gun, you're dead, but who knows. The Waffenampts and Nazi Eagle are stamped on various parts of the gun. The stock is the rare Kriegsmodel version, which is why there is no takedown disc assembly disc by the check, and show signs oh handling wear adding another interesing element. The bore is bright with strong rifling. Im willing to take cash for a face to face transfer in PA, or I can ship to an FFL or C&R FFL if payment is made with a check or moneyorder. Also willing to trade for most C&R guns. Asking $750 obo. I have plenty of more photos, so please email with any questions.
